{
  "stem": "25591.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He met many of them because he came with me to Hungary after a while, but-- but these were just names, and he wrote checks for them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then there were my-- my classmates.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in an amazing way, and I can't tell you how and why, at our last class reunion in September of '96, there must have been 20 of my classmates still very much alive and active, with a very interesting footnote.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When we had a class reunion several years ago, still under the Communist regime, many of my classmates were in-- were in a retirement status.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now there is a free economy and practically all of them are working again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it's a very funny thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, I can think of at least three of them who were physicians, who, when-- when we had the class reunion five years ago, were getting their pension and were retired physicians.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Every single one of them is now actively practicing his profession as a physician, which is sort of an interesting social commentary on what a free economy does to people.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They want to keep working.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At the-- the September meeting they were there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Most of them were Jewish, but some of them were non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, I didn't because-- because I believe-- well, in the case of one of them who was half-Jewish but somehow were not considered Jewish, his family was a very decent family, and they were horrified and appalled by what was happening.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And while I don't think they could do much, they-- they they were on the right side.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
